1
00:00:43,930 --> 00:00:46,900
How do you describe both a beginning and an end?

2
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:49,880
We should have known better.

3
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:51,890
But we didn't.

4
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,690
What does it matter what we think we know?

5
00:00:58,690 --> 00:01:01,560
In the end, there's no denying the truth.

6
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:10,940
Jerusalem, 6:00 PM

7
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:24,850
Iraq, 6:03 PM

8
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:34,460
Syrian - Israeli border, 6:03 PM

9
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:45,920
Mediterranean Sea, 6:04 PM

10
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:54,370
And as the world faces the most serious 
food shortage in history

11
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:56,480
Perhaps there is a ray of hope.

12
00:03:56,550 --> 00:03:58,960
I'm Buck Williams and I'm standing in a wheat field

13
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,700
in the middle of the Israeli desert.

14
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,770
Doctor Rosenzweig...

15
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:06,870
It looks like Iowa!

16
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:09,420
We've truly been blessed with a miracle.

17
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:11,980
One that you have created.

18
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:14,640
Now the biggest question remains:

19
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:16,010
Who do you trust?

20
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:19,060
Every nation, every corporation wants your formula...

21
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,310
especially in the light of the recent crop failures.

22
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:24,610
No, no, no. Eden is not for sale.

23
00:04:25,670 --> 00:04:27,680
Not for money.

24
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:29,730
All I want is

25
00:04:29,730 --> 00:04:32,500
peace for Israel, a peace that...

26
00:04:43,230 --> 00:04:45,610
It looks like the Israeli Air Force never sleeps...

27
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:47,760
Those are not our planes!

28
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:49,720
Not from that direction.

29
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:54,460
Let's take cover!

30
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:56,740
Mr. Williams, please, this way!

31
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:11,620
I want all four commanders to notify the front line.

32
00:06:11,850 --> 00:06:14,750
Put the main squadron into a full state of alert.

33
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,830
This is it.

34
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,560
What's going on? 
 -It's a full-scale air attack.

35
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,080
No warning.

36
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,470
By who?

37
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:25,280
Could be anyone.

38
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:29,970
No one has more enemies who want to 
see her destroyed than Israel.

39
00:06:33,410 --> 00:06:37,070
I don't care if the electronics are jammed; 
get those planes up!

40
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,780
We cannot get our planes up!

41
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,990
It's treachery!

42
00:06:41,990 --> 00:06:44,600
With our technical problems,

43
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,550
they're over Jerusalem!

44
00:06:46,810 --> 00:06:49,420
The Eden Project could've feed the whole world,

45
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:53,610
but now, it is merely going to die with us.

46
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:10,980
Enemy planes are taking direct hits? 
I don't understand.

47
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:14,910
We haven't launched any missiles.

48
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:19,170
Those planes are coming down and we 
haven't fired a shot.

49
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:20,820
It's not possible!

50
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:23,490
They're jamming our monitors, it's a cruel trick.

51
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,960
Only one way to find out.

52
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,960
No, Buck!

53
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,580
This is Buck Williams, reporting live from Israel.

54
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:05,420
I am standing in the middle of an all-out attack.

55
00:08:08,890 --> 00:08:12,520
The sun is gone, thousands of planes are 
soaring overhead.

56
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,730
Fire is raining from the sky.

57
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:16,550
This is just unbelievable!

58
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:20,510
This has got to be the biggest surprise attack 
since Pearl Harbor.

59
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,750
Get out of there, Buck!

60
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:30,610
I've been informed by top-ranking military officials 
that Israel has not been able to launch even a 
single plane in defence. 

61
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:33,820
He would have filmed Hiroshima from ground zero, 
if he would've been there.

62
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:35,270
Yeah, that's our Buck!

63
00:08:35,430 --> 00:08:40,090
As I stand here, fighter planes are exploding 
in mid-air.

64
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:43,720
They're crashing and falling to the ground 
without any explanation.

65
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:49,040
And while no one seems to be able to give me any reason 
for why this is happening, I can tell you this:

66
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:55,180
This all-out, unprecedented attempt to destroy Israel 
appears to be failing.

67
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:09,770
War will continue until the end.

68
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:12,150
Desolations have been decreeted.

69
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:19,150
He will confirm a covenant with many... for 7 years.

70
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:26,700
"Corespondents from the Israeli army deny any connection 
to the destruction of the planes"

71
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:28,680
"..however, inside sources reveal"

72
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,020
Hey, turn that up!
 -Mum said to turn it down.

73
00:10:31,580 --> 00:10:33,860
Do you always do as you're told?
 - Hey, you should try it sometimes.

74
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:36,910
Give me that!

75
00:10:37,530 --> 00:10:39,770
"...for the most reliable and up-to-date information"

76
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:41,420
"I am Buck Williams."

77
00:10:46,410 --> 00:10:48,120
Mum, can you find my art book?

78
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,760
Sure, if you'll help me clean up a little and put up some of these streamers.

79
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,030
No thanks. I am never having kids.

80
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:55,020
Lucky them.

81
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:57,200
Nice touch with the nose-ring, Chloe.

82
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,710
Why not just shave your head and get it over with?

83
00:10:59,710 --> 00:11:00,670
Funny!

84
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,750
I thought your flight didn't leave until midnight?

85
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:05,990
Well, they just called. They want me on the New York - London.

86
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,070
What about Raymie's birthday party?

87
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:13,640
He's all right. Rayme wants that knight's helmet I promised from Buckingham Palace, right pal?

88
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:16,290
Right, or a sword...

89
00:11:16,290 --> 00:11:19,130
or one of those long pointy sticks that they put 
heads on.

90
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:21,930
Don't push it! Where does he come up 
with this stuff?

91
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:23,930
Sunday school!

92
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:29,390
You have to go now? 
-For me to get that helmet, yeah I do.

93
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:39,760
I'll be back in 3 days, all right?

94
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:42,300
OK? 
-all right.

95
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:45,210
See, I told you there's nothing wrong...
-Ray, we've talked about this..

96
00:11:45,210 --> 00:11:47,390
- You knew...
- Look, I don't have any control...

97
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:48,710
Yes you do...you can say no...

98
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,160
Doorbell.

99
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:56,960
Yeah, comming!

100
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:01,090
- Hey, reverend! 
 - Hey, Ray, what's going on?

101
00:12:01,190 --> 00:12:03,270
- Come on in, Bruce!
- Bruce, how's it going?

102
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:04,920
What's that, birthday boy?

103
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,720
- Bruce, where is Jenna. 
- Baby's sick.

104
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:12,180
- Don't throw the ball in the house!
 - Hey, see you, Raymie!

105
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,040
Well, I haven't seen you in a while.

106
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:20,670
People still have to fly, even on Sundays. Excuse me.

107
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:23,310
- Ray!
 - Hey, what did I say?

108
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:25,120
Ray!

109
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:32,120
- I'll see you in a couple of days.
 - OK.

110
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:39,390
- I love you. 
 - Yeah, me too.

111
00:12:40,970 --> 00:12:42,460
Bye!

112
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:50,610
Dad, where are you going?

113
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:53,880
You heard me tell your mother, I have to go to London, 
I have to work.

114
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,880
What about Raymie?

115
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,860
I can see that your bags are all packed, ready to go.

116
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,710
You know I have exams, I have to go.

117
00:13:01,710 --> 00:13:05,110
And I have a flight. It's called a job. 
Welcome to the real world!

118
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:11,280
Your mother has all those people coming over 
and I just can't listen to it...

119
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:14,650
They're not my type of people either, 
but maybe we could show her some support?

120
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:17,420
But what about her respecting what 
the rest of us think, huh?

121
00:13:17,420 --> 00:13:21,550
She's on me too, but I listen. You know, 
sometimes I even pretend to take an interest.

122
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:26,200
- It's not like she's hurting anybody!
 - I wouldn't say that.

123
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:31,420
You know, maybe you should try talking to 
her instead of running away all the time.

124
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:38,550
Good luck on your exams, sweetheart!

125
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,700
Have a safe flight, dad.

126
00:14:02,820 --> 00:14:04,170
GNN Studios, New York

127
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:07,470
Mr. Williams, good to see you back. 
 -Thanks.

128
00:14:10,810 --> 00:14:11,860
Hello!

129
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:15,990
"Dirk Burton. I know who's behind those planes 
falling out of the sky!"

130
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:19,000
- Dirk, what are you talking about?
 - Not on an open line.

131
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,800
"Meet me at the usual spot."

132
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:04,590
The world is in danger, Buck. All of us.

133
00:15:05,350 --> 00:15:09,100
Dirk, just calm down. Knock it down a couple thousand RPMs. 
What's the matter?

134
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:13,420
It's Cothran. I got the file. He thought it was locked, 
but I got it, I got in.

135
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:15,300
What do you know about Rosenzweig?

136
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:16,540
Dirk, what are you talking about?

137
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,700
Don't you see? Chaim Rosenzweig. The formula.

138
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,560
And it's so clear.

139
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:25,920
The attack. The bombers exploding, the flights exploding.

140
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,590
See, see, it's all fitting together now.

141
00:15:28,590 --> 00:15:31,880
I see it, cause they've been behind this 
whole thing from the beginning.

142
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:36,150
The research, the trust funds, and there's the currency.

143
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,440
That's the next step.

144
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:41,290
You see, the dollars, the pounds, the euro, the yemen, 
they're going to make it all into one.

145
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:43,040
One, Buck.

146
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:45,730
Don't you see? It's always about the money, isn't it?

147
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:49,740
What do you know about Rosenzweig. 
He must've said something. Come on!
Think! Think!

148
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:53,060
When is the last time you slept?

149
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:57,940
I'll get all the sleep I need when I'm dead.

150
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:00,950
Rosenzweig.

151
00:16:00,950 --> 00:16:02,950
Come on, Buck, Rosenzweig!

152
00:16:03,190 --> 00:16:06,300
He's a scientist. He's an UN delegate. He's my friend.

153
00:16:06,730 --> 00:16:08,160
Chaim is a good guy.

154
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:11,000
While he might have all the world's best intentions in mind..

155
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,200
But not the guys behind him. Not them for sure!

156
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,100
Who?

157
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:19,450
Cothran and Stonagal.

158
00:16:20,690 --> 00:16:24,240
Those guys are bankers. What do they have to do 
with those planes in Israel?

159
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,200
Ten tracks of land. The whole thing.

160
00:16:27,410 --> 00:16:30,880
But it's gonna go further. Oh, yeah. 
They're not finished.

161
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:33,210
What's next, huh? What's next?

162
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:35,880
Who knows? It's gonna be unimaginable. Here...

163
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:40,650
Look at this. Stonagal's plan for the world.

164
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:44,780
Come on, Dirk. This is an old college essay.

165
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,280
And this...

166
00:16:53,810 --> 00:16:54,800
What's that?

167
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:59,850
Everything from Cothran's computer, 
and all the stuff I've been working on.

168
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:03,700
No, no. I can't give it to you. 
I can't risk you being caught with it.

169
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:05,330
Caught by who?

170
00:17:05,330 --> 00:17:09,670
The NSA, the CIA, the Mossad...

171
00:17:09,670 --> 00:17:12,180
I mean who knows how further this goes..
Dirk, Dirk!

172
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:17,560
You're a nut and I love you. I always have 
and I always will. But come on, man!

173
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:20,930
If you think you got something, then 
give it to me, all right?

174
00:17:21,130 --> 00:17:23,800
Or give it to Alan. We will help you put this thing...

175
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,800
I need more time.

176
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:28,990
Don't worry, Buck. When I get all the pieces in place,

177
00:17:29,330 --> 00:17:32,300
You'll blow Cothran and Stonagal out of the water.
- Dirk...

178
00:17:32,650 --> 00:17:34,300
Promise me you'll do it!

179
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:37,060
Listen. You bring me a story...

180
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:40,100
and you know I'll drive it down to the bone.

181
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:50,990
Get some sleep. Seriously.

182
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:04,840
Can I get you to sign this, Mr. Williams?

183
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:07,070
Must've been a nightmare over there, huh?

184
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,070
Had to get the story.

185
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:09,790
Thanks.

186
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,130
What's he saying?

187
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:21,430
I don't know. It sounds like hebrew.

188
00:18:21,430 --> 00:18:24,200
No. I was there. I heard him. It was english.

189
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:27,290
Amazing you could hear anything with those 
explosions going off everywhere.

190
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:30,070
"What used to be a Third World problem.."

191
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:32,110
"..is now knocking at the door.."

192
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:35,030
"..of even the most prosperous nations."

193
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:39,140
"How can we find peace when people are starving?"

194
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:41,900
Father Theresa!

195
00:18:42,530 --> 00:18:45,780
If we all listened to Carpathia, we'd be one 
big happy family.

196
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,860
Scary would be relating.

197
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:50,570
Speaking of families this just came over the wire.

198
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:54,080
Europe has just standardized their currency with Korea. 
Bizarre, huh?

199
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:57,910
One step closer to a global currency.

200
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:00,160
Come on, darling, I need you.

201
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:05,590
Ivy, see if you can get Dirk Burton 
on the phone for me?

202
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:08,100
Why? Are we doing another story about Area 51?

203
00:19:29,380 --> 00:19:31,380
World peace.

204
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:35,340
It's been a dream ever since Cain 
looked sideways at Cabel.

205
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:39,730
And thanks to your efforts, it can become 
a reality for all of us.

206
00:19:39,990 --> 00:19:43,060
It has only been possible with your support, 
Mr. Stonagal.

207
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:47,010
Ah yes, but you have natural presence, Nikolai.

208
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:51,000
And you give us every confidence in your 
ability to lead the UN.

209
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
Thank you, sir.

210
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,360
Your generosity is overwhelming.

211
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:58,630
It's called money. It gives us that luxury.

212
00:19:59,510 --> 00:20:03,020
Your main concern, the one thing you 
have to worry about..

213
00:20:04,610 --> 00:20:06,460
..is that one issue.

214
00:20:06,460 --> 00:20:08,060
World peace.

215
00:20:08,060 --> 00:20:10,060
Yes, of course.

216
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,130
In your opinion,

217
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:15,020
Will Dr. Rosenzweig accept our proposal?

218
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:18,850
It is an enormous decision for him.

219
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:21,820
He is very close.

220
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:25,260
Maybe this will help convince him?

221
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:32,880
This is incredible.

222
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:37,310
How did you?..

223
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:45,300
Mr. Stonagal, I'm not sure I have the authority to..

224
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:49,950
My friend, if you want events to mirror your desires..

225
00:20:50,230 --> 00:20:52,480
.. You create your own policy.

226
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:56,080
Based on your past successes, 
I'm sure you're right.

227
00:20:56,820 --> 00:20:59,210
And Rosenzweig should know who he can trust.

228
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:02,040
So should you, Nikolai.

229
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:05,700
You know, I can see myself at your age,

230
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:10,110
and I can see your deep concern for 
the global conscience.

231
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:16,280
If I could accomplish even half of what 
you and Mr. Cothran..

232
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:20,210
You will! You will outdistance us. 
We will see to that.

233
00:21:25,330 --> 00:21:27,310
I have a plane waiting for you.

234
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:38,390
Bring us back that olive branch. Good luck!

235
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:53,230
I don't like it, John.

236
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:57,220
Don't worry.

237
00:21:57,220 --> 00:21:59,220
People see him as a hero.

238
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:01,500
And we need a hero to move our plans along.

239
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:05,940
And who will deliver the Arabs? Their children 
cried for hunger, and still they chose war.

240
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:09,420
But I've rearranged some shipments.

241
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:14,010
When their children die of hunger, 
the Arabs will cry for peace.

242
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:16,600
It's all coming together perfectly.

243
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:21,440
Assuming of course, that you've taken care 
of your security problems.

244
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:33,390
